==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sea cocoa
<hw>Sea" co"coa</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A magnificent
palm (<spn>Lodoicea Sechellarum</spn>) found only in the Seychelles
Islands. The fruit is an immense two-lobed nut. It was found floating in
the Indian Ocean before the tree was known, and called <xex>sea
cocoanut</xex>, and <xex>double cocoanut</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sea colander</ent>⟦br⟧
